<subSubSection pageId="64" pageNumber="65" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="64.[189,1399,877,974]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
The South American genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1893" box="[503,617,878,903]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Litoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[503,617,878,903]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Litoporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
now includes 11 nominal species. Three of them occur in 
<taxonomicName box="[1270,1395,877,903]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Venezuela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="64" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Venezuela</taxonomicName>
: the 
<typeStatus box="[232,283,913,939]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Simon, 1893" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1893" box="[383,649,913,939]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Litoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aerius">
<emphasis box="[383,487,913,938]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">L. aerius</emphasis>
Simon, 1893
</taxonomicName>
; the very similar newly described 
<taxonomicName authority="Huber" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2020" box="[1053,1292,913,939]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Litoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curimagua" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1053,1211,913,938]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">L. curimagua</emphasis>
Huber
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1300,1394,913,939]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; and the widespread 
<taxonomicName authority="(Simon, 1893)" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[423,725,948,974]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Litoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uncatus">
<emphasis box="[423,545,949,974]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">L. uncatus</emphasis>
(Simon, 1893)
</taxonomicName>
. All three Venezuelan species are treated below.
</paragraph>
